[[File:City of Rada'a, Yemen, 1909.jpg|thumb|Citadel of Radaa, seen in the back]]
The '''Citadel of Rada'a''' ({{lang-ar|قلعة رداع}}) is a historic castle in [[Yemen]], located in the center of [[Rada'a District]]. The citadel sits at the highest point of the district, and consisted the original part of the city of Rada'a. The construction of the citadel precedes the introduction of [[Islam]] and dates back to the year 243 during the reign of [[Shammar Yahri'sh]], the [[Himyarite]] king.<ref>[https://www.skynewsarabia.com/web/article/42872/%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%87%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%94%D9%83%D8%A8%D8%B1-%D9%82%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%AE%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%86 انهيار أكبر قلعة تاريخية في اليمن]. ''Sky News Arabia''. Retrieved January 4, 2018.</ref> Specifically, the upper part of the citadel dates back to the Hymyarite era. Later the citadel was restored and renovated during the time of Omar bin Abdulwahhab of the [[Tahirids (Yemen)|Tahirids dynasty]]. During this time, the other parts of the citadel were added, and the construction was ended during the time of Imam Yahya Hamid al-Din, who used the castle as a prison for the rebels. Its status as a prison lasted until the 1990s.<ref>[http://almoheet.net/%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%B1%D9%81-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%82%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A9-%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%AE%D9%8A%D8%A9/ تعرف على قلعة رداع التاريخية.] ''Al-Moheet''. Retrieved January 4, 2018.</ref>
In September 2012, the western part of the citadel had collapsed due to the rainwater and the lack of proper maintenance and restoration.<ref>[https://www.yemeress.com/almotamar/101458 انهيار الجانب الغربي من قلعة رداع التاريخية]. ''Yemress''. Retrieved January 4, 2018.</ref>
