'''Malays in Egypt''' make up a part of the [[overseas Malays|overseas Malay]] population. [[Malaysian language|Malay speakers]] who came to [[Egypt]] are mainly from [[Malaysia]] and [[Indonesia]]. In 1927, they started a newspaper, ''Seruan Azhar''.<ref>{{citation|title=Indonesian and Malay Students in Cairo in the 1920s|journal=Indonesia|volume=9|date=April 1970|pages=73&ndash;87|last=Roff|first=William R.|jstor=3350623|doi=10.2307/3350623|publisher=Southeast Asia Program Publications at Cornell University|issue=9}}</ref>

